column4: >The use of the iPad as a communication and educational tool is increasing in record numbers. With over 650,000 apps and counting, many parents, professionals, and speech language pathologists are seeking guidance on how to properly select and use apps to maximize learning potential.

>This 1.5 hour webinar will explore how to enable the iPad settings for educational success, use the SETT framework to make effective Assistive Technology decisions, and review a 4 step evidence-based app implementation plan to elicit the most language, communication and socialization skills.
column7: >Language, socialization, and communication apps will be discussed as well as creative ways to generalize outside of the app.

column4: >State 2 features of the iPad that can be used to enhance communication and learning.
>Define and state the features of the SETT framework and how it helps guide to make effective Assistive Technology decisions.
>Explain each of the 4 components of the app implementation plan.
>State 2 apps that can be used in the areas of language, socialization and communication.

alt=""Belvoir Lodge Gardens and Fountains"" width=""340"" height=""295"" />
Join Vista, the local charity dedicated to improving lives for people with sight loss in Leicester, Leicestershire and Rutland, for an opportunity to view the beautifully renovated private gardens of Her Grace, Dowager Duchess of Rutland.

column4:
>You can take in a breathtaking view of the Vale of Belvoir whilst enjoying an afternoon of live music and enjoy a cream tea and refreshments! Tickets cost £4* in advance (*booking fee applies)and £6 on the door. A complimentary drink is included in the ticket price.

When someone first finds out that they are losing their sight, they are often devastated and need help to come to terms with their new situation.  Individuals wonder how they will manage to get out and about, how they will manage everyday tasks in the home like cooking or gardening, how they will be able to continue working.

>
This is where Vista has been helping since 1858 by providing information and practical support, specialist equipment and training to help people to regain their confidence and independence. 

For the many people with sight loss isolated at home, Vista offers social activities and *Befriending opportunities to reduce loneliness and get people involved in their local community again.

column5: >*Befriending is funded by the Big Lottery.

column1:
",vistablind.org.uk,1339673507,1347231600,1340313225.0,1347217200,0,0,1.0,1,y,Jazz in the Garden,18,3734338,"

Hello, we're Vista!

Vista is a charity that is dedicated to improving the lives of people with sight loss in Leicester, Leicestershire and Rutland. Every year Vista provides services, support, advice and information to almost 6000 registered blind and partially sighted local people.

Support Vista in our vision of a world in which people with sight loss of all ages have choice and control over their lives and no-one experiences avoidable sight loss.

Dr. Susan Lawton and Rebecca Hintze address the psychological and physical remedies necessary to live an abundant life!  Dr. Lawton, a clinical psychologist and biochemist brings more than 40 years of clinical experience and combines her expertise with the wisdom of Rebecca Hintze, family issues expert and author of the international bestseller, ""Healing Your Family History.""  Among many shared interests, these two experts share their love of doTERRA essential oils and they will teach attendees how to heal both mind and body, and  break free of destructive patterns, with doTERRA remedies and the power of thought and intention.  Join these two energetic and fun ladies for a night you'll remember forever!  Seating is limited.  This event will sell out fast! (This event has already sold out twice and the Marriott has extended our room size to make more seats available.  This is the last time we can add more seats.  We hope each of you are able to get the tickets you need.)

column2: >Act 3 one of  series of linked walks covering the life of  Shakespeare in London tracks Shakespeare and his King's Men acting company as they transfer across the river to the West End (of the City of London). Find the old Blackfriars theatre site and the priory gatehouse bought by the now rich playwright. Visit pubs and other buildings known by the Bard and stand near the site of his Silver Street lodgings.

column1: YWiB is partnering with Vancouver Whitecaps FC to host a dynamic discussion between you, your peers and an amazing panel surrounding topics of bringing lessons learned in sports to the business world. Specifically, the panelists will touch upon the topics of setting out to accomplish your vision/dream, teamwork and skill development.
• Rachel Lewis, COO of Vancouver Whitecaps FC
• Carly Jokic, Director of Communications of Vancouver Whitecaps FC

Tickets: $40 - includes light appies, engaging panel session and Whitecaps match (reg. $39)
tickets to the match will be available at the entrance to the BC Place conference room at the start of the event
Time: 5:30pm panel session, followed by a 7pm Whitecaps match
Appies and snacks are included - we encourage you to bring your favourite sports waterbottle to be sustainable!
Some of the questions and topics that we'll be discussing:
Q: How do you communicate your vision to the team in the office, the fans, players? How are you all working together to accomplish this?
Q: The Whitecaps have experienced a lot of change in the past few years, becoming an MLS team, how have you managed your growing team and the changes in the office and on the field?
Q: How do you manage the different needs of the people you lead?
Q: Do you recognize similarities in your approach to developing your soccer skills to how you learn to do other things and approach other challenges?

Q: How did you know what skills to focus on learning? As goal oriented women, we're told to develop numerous skills and it can be overwhelming to know what to focus on first. How did you prioritize and know waht you focus your energy on to become successful in your goals?

column4: >The beginning of 2012 saw continued strength in the early stage financing environment with valuations and the number of financings increasing, a trend that continued from 2011. However, as the year has progressed concerns about an over-heated investment market have been replaced with a perception of a weakening funding environment. 2011 was viewed by some as the year of the founder/entrepreneur and by others as the year of the &ldquo
column6: and excess valuations, with many more new angels expected to enter the market following the IPOs of several high profile companies. However, in 2012 venture investment appears to have softened considerably and may be in a state of transition with the funding environment less robust. In addition, the renewed strength of the public and secondary trading markets seen in 2011 has abated somewhat following Facebook&rsquo
column7: s IPO and the US and world economies remain weak.&nbsp

column4: >Against this backdrop, the VC industry is undergoing profound changes and seed/angel funds have become more active than ever before. Please join our panel of expert angel and venture capital investors for a look at early stage investing during the past year and what the future investment environment holds. The presentation will also include a review of the key metrics for venture capital investments/exits and critical VC term sheet terms for Q2 2012. This will be a thought provoking and informative session you will not want to miss!

column1: -No More Frustration, 1-On-1 with a Facebook Guru, And seats are selling fast!
Facebook can be a hard thing to master without someone to guide you. Most of us rely on our children to show us, but that rarely ends in success.. rather more frustration and more questions. Right?
So the question is: Are you struggling with facebook?

If you thought about using Facebook for your business, and or using Facebook, but not getting results ... NOW is the time to attend this affordable class.  With a limited audience, you will be guaranteed to walk away with value.

Make this decision today not someday.

Stop those struggles today by joining Trey Lewellen as he shows you, step by step, the facebook basics.
You will have 4 Hours with Trey Lewellen for one on one time and be able to ask the hard questions!
You will need to bring a Laptop, a networking cable that is at least 5 foot long, and a notepad for notetaking.
We will see you on the inside!
Still undecided if this is for you? Contact Darlene Simmons at 314-378-2163 for more details.
Before you go, connect with Trey by clicking on the following links: Facebook | YouTube | Twitter | Blog

column5: >September Luncheon: The Advocate's Entry Into New Orleans

column6: >Featuring guest speaker: David Manship, publisher and CEO of The Advocate

column5: >With the recent changes to the overall structure of The Times-Picayune, the media landscape in New Orleans is forever changing. The absence of a daily newspaper is providing an opportunity for other outlets, such as The Advocate, to step up to the plate and fulfill a gap in what has become a significant part of the daily routines of New Orleans residents. Listen as the publisher and CEO of The Advocate discusses his plans for expanding coverage of the Baton Rouge paper into the New Orleans area and best practices for working with his staff.

>About David Manship - Manship received his elementary school education in East Baton Rouge Parish public schools. He is a graduate of Sewanee Military Academy in Sewanee, Tennessee and of DeVry Institute of Technology in Dallas. He served in the United States Army from 1968 - 1971. In 1973, Manship began his career in Baton Rouge at The Advocate, Saturday and Sunday Advocate - working in all areas of the company. In 1985, he was named vice president - sales and marketing and became associate publisher in 1989. He served as publisher from 1991 to 1999, returning to the Publisher's Office in 2007. Manship is a past president of the Louisiana Press Association and the Arts Council of Greater Baton Rouge. He currently serves on the board of directors of Capital City Press, Louisiana Television and Broadcast Corporation and Mobile Video Tapes and has served board positions for a number of organizations over the years. In 1984, Manship was one of 13 individuals who received the President's Award from the LSU Foundation for meritorious support of higher education. In 1989, he was presented the SMEI Marketer of the Year Award.

Join us on November 15 for the 2012 MaRS Future of Medicine conference.

This years conference will build on the success of the previous three years with a focus on market access for medical technology.

The conference will feature:
• Presentations by international experts speaking on different aspects of device development and commercialization
• An industry panel discussion on medtech reimbursement  who are the payers?
• A pitch showcase of emerging startups in the medical device and health IT sectors
• An exhibit of past, present and future innovations

and more!

Medical technology innovators will have the opportunity for education and networking, and industry members will be able to exhibit their business and source the most exciting innovations in the sector. If you are working or interested in medtech commercialization, then this is the conference for you.
We look forward to seeing you at the MaRS Future of Medicine™ 2012 Annual Conference!
*Advance registration closes at 5:00 p.m. on November 14. Walk-in registration will be available the morning of the conference for $125.00. Register now to secure your spot!

*Please note that all sales are final. MaRS reserves the right to grant refunds only on a case-by-case basis.

column4: >Are you passionate about a certain issue or topic? Do you want to make change happen?
>Learn how to turn your passion into a reality by starting a nonprofit organization. This seminar covers the key steps to start and successfully run a nonprofit organization, including: nonprofit
column9: >incorporation, nonprofit management structure and roles, fundraising for nonprofit organizations, and more!

column4: >This lecture-style seminar is four hours long and includes interactive discussions. Participants are encouraged to share their issue and/or topic of interest. The general outline of the workshop is:

>This seminar will be facilitated by Heather Carpenter and Terry Horton. Carpenter is an experienced nonprofit manager, researcher, trainer, and blogger. She earned her M.M. in Nonprofit Administration from North Park University in Chicago, Ill. and her Ph.D. in Leadership Studies from the University of San Diego where she served as a research associate in the Caster Family Center for Nonprofit and Philanthropic Research. She teaches and presents on a variety of topics in the nonprofit sector, is an avid social media user and authors the well-known Nonprofit Leadership 601 blog.

>Carpenter is also the author and creator of three nonprofit management toolkits: Nonprofit Operations, Setting up a Nonprofit Office, and Starting a Nonprofit, and her current research interests include: nonprofit education, nonprofit workforce, and nonprofit technology. She participates on a variety of national nonprofit committees and partners with many national nonprofit organizations to promote and support nonprofit careers and the nonprofit sector.

>Horton has a J.D. from Lewis and Clark Law School in Portland, Ore. and was previously a consultant for The Foraker Group, a management support organization serving nonprofit organizations throughout the state of Alaska.

column4: >Nearly five years ago, we realized a dream in starting Green Spaces. Growing the organization into the coworking homebase of incredible social entrepreneurs in New York and Colorado has been (and is still!) a remarkable journey. And now, our community has grown so strong that I think we're ready to evolve.
>Here's the question: how do we scale community?
>Incidentally, I'm turning 32 on August 7th. Birthday reflections on my year led to an ""Aha!"" moment. <span style=""font-size: 12pt
column5: >On my 32nd, I'd love nothing more than to celebrate with you - and ask for your help in answering that tough question. Flockd: For Real World Connections
column6: >is my new startup and a communication technology designed to scale connection and build spirited movements.

column4: >Regardless of whether you join us, you have my gratitude for being a part of the fire that keeps me going!

column3: >5.05pm - The Australian Property Investment Markets - Presented by Anthony De Francesco, IPD

>Anthony joined IPD in October 2009 as Managing Director. IPD (Investment Property Databank) is the world leader in performance analysis for the owners, investors, managers and occupiers of real estate. Anthony is responsible for the delivery of products and services which include: real estate portfolio performance analysis
column4: market indices, and customised research projects. Anthony has over twelve years experience in various research roles. Anthony&rsquo
column5: s research experience involved developing house views on Australian property markets, reviewing international markets (both economic and property fundamentals) and undertaking strategic research on real asset investment markets. Anthony has held a variety of roles that included Head of Research &ndash
column6: Property and Infrastructure, Colonial First State Global Asset Management
column7: Head of Research, Colonial First State Property
column8: Senior Quantitative Analyst with Commsec, Commonwealth Bank of Australia and Head of Research with Lend Lease Real Estate Investments Ltd. Anthony is actively involved in education programs for the property industry and various educational tertiary level institutions. He presents at various industry forums and for private clients and actively publishes in academic research journals.

column3: >Anthony will provide analysis of property investments markets and address the following questions
column4: where are we in the current cycle, what is the outlook for property and how is Queensland faring compared with the rest of Australia? He will also introduce the Green Property Index and the Capex Index. These tools are helping building owners and managers focus their efforts on where to invest their capital to best enhance returns for their investors.

column5: Benchmarking - Presented by Nicola Wooward, MBMpl Pty Ltd

column3: >Nicola has been with MBM for a year since their acquisition of Apex Property Consulting where she was a founding Director.<span style=""mso-spacerun: yes
column5: Nicola is dual qualified in valuation and tax and has spent the last 15 years analysing capital expenditure. Initially this was for tax purposes, but Nicola realised that the data she was gathering was of far greater use than just claiming tax deductions. In conjunction with her clients she developed a capital expenditure benchmarking tool that is being used for capex planning. MBM are sponsors of the IPD Capex Index.

column3: >Nicola will be discussing capital expenditure data: where it comes from, how you can use it, how you can use it to forecast future expenditure and the impact it has on investment returns.

column3: >In the ever changing world of social media, radio presenters and producers need to stay on top of what the technology offers to best engage their audiences. In this short session, social media radio experts from Somethin' Else
column4: will showcase some of their award winning case studies and explain how best to manage the most recent changes in Facebook and Twitter.

column3: >Participants will be divided into small groups to creatively tackle a social media problem that they face in their own radio production, these will be presented back to the main group for feedback. This session is aimed at women in audio who already have a good practical awareness of social media but are in need of further guidance and ideas on how to best integrate it into their programme making.
>The course will be run by Nicky Birch, Head of Radio Development at Somethin' Else, the UK's leading content design agency and
column6: Producer of the acclaimed Radio 1's Review Show, Nan Davies.

column3: >Nicky's role is to develop radio and digital ideas, respond to radio and interactive tenders from the BBC and commercial brands and she also produces David Rodigan on BBC Radio 2 winning a Sony Gold in 2012 for Best Specialist programme.&nbsp
column4: Please bring your laptop / ipad and headphones to work on during the session.

column4: >Join GLI's EnterpriseCorp's Tendai Charasika along with guest speaker, angel investor and business coach Greg Langdon, as they discuss the crucial elements of building your investor pitch deck.

“Creating The Perfect Pitch Deck”

Based on the collective experience of actively reviewing and improving hundreds of investor pitch decks per year, our guest presenters will share with entrepreneurs tips and tricks on creating a winning investor presentation.
>Tendai and Greg have helped numerous early stage startup companies prepare and revise their pitches in hopes of securing the ultimate goal - Startup funding!

column6: >Does your preschooler think the world revolves around them?<span style=""mso-spacerun: yes

column6: >Whether being moody, throwing tantrums or just being very busy, preschoolers often bring new challenges for parents. Join <span style=""color: #bc00bc

column15: >GRASP group is a collaboration of a Psychotherapist and a Child Developmental Specialist who provide consultation, therapy, support groups and education.

column6:
>Our mission at GRASP is to meet parents where they are in their quest for achieving a healthy partnership and bonding experience with their child/ren. Whether the goal is to address post-partum emotional challenges, bonding with your little one, reconnecting in your intimate relationship, finding support for a new stage of life or learning about effective ways to parent, our practitioners take the time to listen and understand the unique needs of each client and give you tools to transform your relationships.

column11: > is an innovative and interactive practice-based educational program that provides pharmacists with the skills necessary to become primary sources for vaccine advocacy, education, and administration. The program reviews the basics of immunology, identifies legal and regulatory issues pharmacists must consider before starting an immunization program, and focuses on practice implementation.

column5: >The purpose of this educational program is to:

column16: >Provide comprehensive immunization education and training.
>Provide pharmacists with the knowledge, skills, and resources necessary to establish and promote a successful immunization service.
>Teach pharmacists to identify at-risk patient populations needing immunizations.
><font face=""Calibri""><font size=""3"">Teach pharmacists to administer immunizations in compliance with legal and regulatory standards.<span style=""mso-spacerun: yes

column9: > is conducted in two parts: the self-study and the live training.<span style=""mso-spacerun: yes
column11: >A Certificate of Achievement will be awarded to participants who successfully complete all program components, including an evaluation form. Statements of Credit and Certificates will be issued within 4-6 weeks of APhA's receipt of program materials.

column6: >Key learning objectives for the live training seminar are:

column15: >Identify opportunities for pharmacists to become involved in immunization delivery.
>Describe how vaccines evoke an immune response and provide immunity.

column14: >Identify the vaccines available on the U.S. market for each vaccine-preventable disease and classify each vaccine as live attenuated or inactivated.

>Evaluate a patient’s medical and immunization history and determine in the patient falls into the target groups for each vaccine based on the Advisory Committee for Immunization Practices (ACIP) recommendations.

column15: >Review a patient case and determine patient-specific vaccine recommendations based on the appropriate immunization schedule.

column14: >Discuss the legal, regulatory, and liability issues involved with pharmacy-based immunization programs.

column15: >Describe the signs and symptoms of adverse reactions that can occur after vaccination
>Describe the emergency procedures for management of patients with adverse reactions to vaccination.

column14: >List the steps for appropriate intranasal administration technique for the live attenuated influenza vaccine.

column15: >Demonstrate appropriate intramuscular and subcutaneous injection technique for adult immunization.

column9: >or a complete list of learning objectives, please go to APhA’s website, www.pharmacist.com/ctp/immunization.

column16: >The Importance of Vaccines and The Pharmacist’s Role in Vaccine Delivery
>How Do Vaccines Prevent Disease?
>Establishing a Pharmacy-Based Immunization Program
>Adverse Events Following Vaccination and Emergency Preparedness

column8: >

column10: >Karen K. O'Brien B.S. Pharm., Pharm. D.
>Linda K. Ohri, Pharm.D., MPH
>Alicia C. Vanden Bosch, Pharm.

column5: ><font size=""3""><font face=""Calibri"">Successful completion of the live seminar component involves passing the final exam with a grade of 70% or higher and demonstrating competency in 2 intramuscular and 1 subcutaneous injection. Successful completion of this component will result in 8.0 contact hours of continuing pharmacy education credit (0.80 CEUs).<span style=""mso-spacerun: yes

><font size=""3""><font face=""Calibri"">Successful completion of the self-study component involves passing the self-study assessment questions with a grade of 70% or higher and will result in 12.0 contact hours of continuing pharmacy education credits (1.2 CEUs).<span style=""mso-spacerun: yes

column3: >This 3 day course provides training for administrators with the fundamentals key to having a successful implementation and maintenance of a Hadoop cluster.&nbsp
column4: The course consists an effective mix of interactive lecture and extensive hands-on lab exercises.
>By taking this course, administrators are provided with the following:

column3: >Experience of installing, configuring, deploying, verifying and maintaining Hadoop clusters
>Experience with hardware upgrade process of removing node, changing configuration, installing new node and rebalancing the cluster.
>Cluster Hardware and Installation of HDFS and MapReduce
>Monitor, Maintain and Troubleshoot HDFS and MapReduce
>Install Configure, Deploy and Verify HBase and ZooKeeper
>Install Configure, Deploy and Verify Other Hadoop Ecosystem (HCatalog, Oozie, Mahout)
>Install Configure, Deploy and Verify Nagios and Ganglia

column6: >Students will work through the following exercises using the Hortonworks Data Platform:

column4: >All Hadoop logs for core, HDFS and MapReduce
>Using fsck and Taking Action on Output
>Install Configure, Deploy and Verify HBase and ZooKeeper
>Install configure and use Nagios and Ganglia

column3: >Administrators who are interested in learning how to deploy and manage a Hadoop cluster.
>We recommend students have previous experience with UNIX.&nbsp
>Facility Details including directions, parking, hotel recommendations, and more.
>Please contact us at hwuniversity@hortonworks.com if you have any questions and/or comments.

>
You must provide a written notice to Hortonworks at least 2 weeks prior to the start of the class if you cannot attend this class.
column5: transfer your registration to a future class of equal or lesser value.

column2: >Hortonworks can cancel up to 2 week prior to the course start date. In the event that the class is cancelled, we will work with you to apply your registration to another date or refund your fee in full.

column7:
>Hortonworks is focused on accelerating the development and adoption of Apache Hadoop. Together with the Apache community, we are making Hadoop more robust and easier to use for enterprises and more open and extensible for solution providers. We also provide expert support and training.

column7: > The O’Daniel Jeep Jam Cornhole Event is open to any persons 12 years of age or older. Individuals ranked as Super-Pro or Pro Caliber as listed on the American Cornhole Organization website are not eligible to play. Those ranked as semi-pro and amateurs will be permitted.
> The O’Daniel group will accept team registrations beginning September 25th. Teams will be accepted into the tournament until October 12
column10: > or when 50 teams officially register, whichever occurs first. Each team will pay a $25 registration fee before the entry will be accepted. Players must register in teams of two players. Single entries will not be accepted. Registration fees are non-refundable.

column7: > Entries received by mail will be accepted based on the date the entry is received at O’Daniel Auto Group.
column11: > Refunds will ONLY be given to teams if they meet one of the criterion listed below:

column4: >The tournament reaches 50 teams and your registration was accepted online after that time.
>Registration fees will NOT be refunded for any other reason. If a team pays the registration fee and becomes unable to participate at a later date, the registration fee is forfeited.

column7: > The ODZ Jeep Jam Cornhole Event will be played as a single elimination bracket tournament. On Saturday, October 13
column10: > 50 teams will compete in a bracket tournament. During tournament play each team will play their assigned opponent at their assigned time (competitors are chosen at random prior to the tournament) If any team is more than 10 minutes late FOR ANY REASON, the team will forfeit their participation and a stand-by team will be accepted for the remainder of the tournament. Teams will play best-2-out-of-3 games to 21 points. This guarantees each team at least 2 games during the tournament.  Players will be responsible for keeping their score using the scoring devices provided at each cornhole game set.  There will be no Skunk rule in this tournament.

column7: > One (1) grand prize of half of all money raised from the cornhole tournament will be given.  For instance, if 50 teams register at $25 per team, the grand prize would be $625.

> The ODZ Jeep Jam Cornhole Event will be played and operated by the official cornhole rules as regulated by the American Cornhole Organization (ACO). These rules can be found at <a href=""http://www.americancornhole.org""><span style=""text-decoration: underline
column9:
>www.americancornhole.org. ODZ highly suggests that all players review these rules and be familiar with them prior to playing in our tournament.  All ACO game rules will be strictly enforced with the exception of the Skunk rule. Players are responsible for making themselves aware of the scoring, fouls and general game rules associated with Cornhole prior to taking part in the tournament.

",me.com,1348781425,1350169200,1348781600.0,1350169200,0,0,0.0,1,y,"ODZ JEEP JAM 2012

column4: >Please remember to start your tour at 2326 Esplanade Ave on Saturday November 3rd and 4725 Dauphine St on Sunday November 4th. These locations will have your tickets, wristbands, maps and commemorative posters!

column5: > is once again opening doors to the city's elegant and eclectic homes and studios for the 3rd Annual weekend of tours presented by the Creative Alliance of New Orleans, (CANO). This is one of the nation's largest tours, this year of over 40 homes and studios.

> is an annual self-guided public tour, this year on November 3rd and 4th from 12-5pm. The tour highlights emerging artists as well as works in private art collections. One participant said of last year’s tour: “You can go to galleries and museums anytime, but to meet the artists and see the art in private collections brings out the essence of the city.”

>: The tour includes homes and studios citywide on Saturday, November 3rd and in the Lower 9th Ward on Sunday, November 4th, from 12pm to 5pm on both days. Some of the artists included this year are Prospect.2’s Bruce Davenport Jr., blacksmith Rachel David, painter Nicole Charbonnet, sculptor, Clifton Webb, photographers Kevin Kline, and Christopher Porche West, the home of Enrique Alferez’s daughter Tlaloc Alferez and many more!

column3: >Also enjoy ""wrap parties"" at the end of the tours at Casa Borrega, 1719 Oretha Castle Haley Boulevard at 5pm on Saturday, and at the Art House on the Levee, 4725 Dauphine Street, at 5pm on Sunday night.

>How: With the purchase of tickets, tour participants receive a map that guides them through the city visiting these vibrant, private locations. Tickets are $15/day and $25/weekend. Student tickets are $10/day. Tickets can be purchased online at

column5: 3rd consecutive year in which estate and gift tax laws are in a state of substantial flux.&nbsp
column7: changed unpredictably and ranged widely in the last several years. The New Year is expected to herald substantial new changes once again.&nbsp

column3: >Join WIFS NE FL for lunch as Jeff Cramer with <a href=""http://www.cramerlawcenter.com"" target=""_blank"">Cramer Law&nbsp
column4: Center reviews the current issues in Estate Planning for 2013.
column5: Jeff will provide a practical guide to major changes in the estate and gift tax law, planning opportunities under the new tax regime, and a discussion of how changed law impacts existing plans.

column1: Jeffrey A. Cramer holds an undergraduate degree from Vanderbilt University and a Doctor of Jurisprudence (J.D.), with honors, from the University of Florida College of Law, where he served on the Editorial Board of the Law Review.
column2: He has been admitted to practice law in all state and federal courts in Florida.&nbsp
column3: With more than 34 years experience as a civil trial lawyer, Jeff successfully has handled a wide variety of personal injury and employment-discrimination claims, contract and family disputes, as well as probate and guardianship contests in both trial and appellate courts.&nbsp
column4: Jeff also has been an adjunct professor of employment law at Florida Coastal School of Law, a frequent lecturer at continuing legal education seminars and has published several articles on civil trial issues.

column2: >Jeff has been certified by the Florida Supreme Court as both a circuit court and family mediator. He has received the highest rating from his peers, &ldquo
column4: by the Martindale-Hubbell Company, is listed in the &ldquo
column10: Jeff has served as Escambia-Santa Rosa County Bar Association President and both as Northwest Florida Chapter President and member of the National Board of Directors of the prestigious American Board of Trial Advocates.

column2: >The extensive trial experience gathered from handling thousands of diverse civil matters has provided the skills necessary for Jeff to embark on the next phase of his career, helping people and families to plan effectively for their future.&nbsp
column3: Jeff undertook a several month course of intensive study of all facets of estate planning and now focuses his law practice on estate planning, estate administration (including probate), guardianship and elder law.&nbsp
column4: He is a member of the National Network of Estate Planning Attorneys, an experienced, cutting-edge group of forward thinking lawyers who collaborate and educate on the latest estate planning laws and techniques.&nbsp
column5: Jeff also is a certified legacy advisor helping clients pass on their wisdom along with their wealth. As a result, his law practice now offers clients the combination of the support of a group of experienced estate planning colleagues from around the country along with Jeff&rsquo
column6: s own extensive legal background and experience.

The Calgary Sports Convention, known as the YYC SportsCon, will be the first ever event of this calibre held in Canada, where the latest and greatest gadgets, companies, retailers, information from the sports industry will be on display under one roof.
There will also be celebrities/athletes attending, allowing fans an opportunity to get autographs and/or pictures with some of their favourite stars.
The convention will run from August 16th to August 18th, 2013. There are different ticket options available, allowing you to choose the one that best suits your needs.
Are there ID requirements or an age limit to enter the event?
No, there is no age limit. However, there are different ticket prices for different ages.
What are my transport/parking options getting to the event?
You can use the Calgary Transit to get to Stampede Park, or you may park at the Stampede Grounds for a fee.
Where can I contact the organizer with any questions?
If you have any questions, you can send them to contact@yycsportscon.com, and put the heading ""Tickets"" in the subject line of your email. We will do our best to respond to you within 48 hours.
Do I have to bring my printed ticket to the event?
Yes, you will need to show your printed ticket at the door to gain admission to the Big Four Building, where YYC SportsCon is being held.
What if I bought tickets, but can't go anymore. Can I give/sell them to a friend?
Although the name of the individual that purchased the ticket shows up on there, the barcodes are unique so you can give it to anybody you like. We can still track them.
What if I bought tickets, but can't go anymore. Can I get a refund?

Unfortunately, there are no refunds or exchanges on any tickets purchased. This applies to any and all circumstances, unless the convention is canceled by the hosting company. If that happens, then all ticket purchases will be refunded to all ticket purchasers within 30 business days.

Howard Men's Lacrosse will be hosting a Lacrosse Combine Sunday November 18th. The Combine will take place at Howard's Greene Stadium featuring a series of events including 40 yard dash, fastest shot, trick shot competition, and more. All participants will receive a personalized stat sheet recording all of their results. There will be music, refreshment, and prizes throughout the day. The event is open to both males and female of all ages and skill levels. Participants under 18 will require parental consent. NO CLEATS OR SPIKED SHOES.
column2:
Registration is $10 per participant, $7 for Early Registration (before Sunday November 18th). Participants may bring their own lacrosse sticks. Basic sticks will be provided for those that do not have their own. Check in and Late Registration will begin at 10am and will close promptly at 11am. After the conclusion of the Combine, feel free to stay and see the Howard Lacrosse Alumni Reunion Game as the current Bison lacrosse team faces off against the the Bison lacrosse alumni. For questions or concerns please contact us at info@bison-lax.com.

",bison-lax.com,1352816993,1353285000,1352819963.0,1353261600,0,0,,1,y,HU Lacrosse Combine & Alumni Game,33,4816089,"

Howard Men's Lacrosse was started as a club sport in 1989 at Howard University in Washington, DC. Howard University is one of only four HBCUs to have a Men's lacrosse program including Morgan State, Hampton, and Morehouse. With support from the students, the faculty, our fans, and all other minority organizations we hope to continue our journey towards excellence in the game of Lacrosse and grow together as brother. HU! You Know!

Enter the world of the digital SLR and learn about your camera, and how to make great pictures with it. We'll take you out of ""automatic"", but we won't overload you with too much detail.

You'll see many examples of great photography, and learn techniques to use exposure, composition, flash, and a variety of lenses to get the same types of results. Our Basic Discovery Day class is a three-hour investment in your EOS digital SLR that will pay dividends over and over as you grow with your camera system.

During this course you will:

* Become familiar with the operation and features of your EOS camera, and discover how and when to control them for dramatic results
* Learn to expand your creative options, using different camera features and photographic techniques to evolve your pictures from snapshots to photographs
* See actual examples of how Canon lenses and Speedlite flashes can be used to add impact to your pictures
PARKING: Parking is available through Holiday Inn for $10/day. Metered street parking is also available.

Creative Soul Entertainment and friends would like to express their sincerest gratitude by hosting an Appreciation Party.  This party is dedicated to the supporters. From family, friends, artists to vendors, sponsors, and venue owners: This party is for YOU!
My vision, my goals, my crazy imagination could not have happened without the support from all of you!
So many people who believed in this project and continue to communicate to others about the existence of this sexy event is a GREAT FEELING!
How else to celebrate this chapter in the ""Unleash"" saga?  Have a party and bring everyone who has put their 2 cents in, showed some skin, and made the audience smile.
So come for awhile and spend some time with me and the rest of the Unleash family.
• A video viewing of our last show (Dvd's are for sale)
• A special presentation to get you ready for the next show!
Guests could purchase their 2013 Unleash Calendar and Erika's poetry book, ""Unleashed"" in advance. Your reserved book will be at the party along with a special gift.

This event is FREE and open to adults only.

column3: ><em><font size=""2"">Erika Jarvis was born in Chicago, Illinois and grew up in Rogers Park.  She began her formal dance training with Deidre Dawson, at Roger C. Sullivan High School.<span style=""mso-spacerun: yes
column4: >  As Erika’s mentor and “second mom”, Ms. Dawson opened opportunities for her to audition and receive a scholarship from Joseph Holmes Chicago Dance Theater.
column5: >  After graduating from Sullivan High School, she attended Columbia College Chicago with a focus on Dance Education.   Her training with Krenly Guzman, Dardi McGinley, and Shirley Mordine inspired her to continue her studies and contribute to the dance community.
column6: >  Ms. Jarvis has performed and choreographed for companies, television, and artists.
column8: >  Cirque De Soleil, Dave Scott, Red Eye Newspaper, Barcardi Silver, Kraft Foods, Latin Street Dancing, Boogie McClarin, Dance Chicago, Miss Black Illinois Pageant, L.I.F.E., Mr. A.L.I., Quentin De Alexander, Jenny Jones Show, Miller Genuine Draft, City of Chicago, and several youth organizations throughout the Midwest.

column3: font-family: Arial, Helvetica, 'Bitstream Vera Sans', sans-serif
column6: >Shannon Galpin founded Mountain2Mountain in November 2006. A rape survivor and mother, she realized she couldn&rsquo
column7: t just stand on the sidelines, watching women and girls routinely raped, oppressed and denied basic human rights. Believing that connecting communities on both sides of the equation was key to combating the apathy that prevents action and that changing perceptions was just as important as tangible projects, she developed events that involved communities and provoked discussion through art, music, and sport.

column3: font-family: Arial, Helvetica, 'Bitstream Vera Sans', sans-serif
column6: >After four years working in various parts of Afghanistan working with women and girls, Shannon developed long-term strategies that focused on cyclical solutions in conflict zones globally that focused on connecting communities and sparking conversation. &nbsp
column7: It was in the Kandahar prison, where Shannon was confronted with the power of voice. &nbsp
column8: Frustrated by the lack of tangible help she would be able to provide, she was overwhelmed by the outpouring of stories from the women. &nbsp
column9: They were despereate to be heard, to know that their injustice, their struggle, their heartbreak would survive outside of those walls. &nbsp

column3: font-family: Arial, Helvetica, 'Bitstream Vera Sans', sans-serif
column6: >An avid mountain biker continually focused on breaking gender barriers, in 2009, she became the first woman to mountain bike in Afghanistan, a country where the culture does not allow women to ride bikes. In 2010 she became the first person to ride across Afghanistan&rsquo
column7: s Panjshir Valley, which gave birth to the&nbsp
column9: href=""http://www.panjshirtour.org/"">Panjshir Tour, a series of community bike rides in the US.
column10: Along the way, she always has a silver barette given to her by one of the women inside the Kandahar prison - a piece of that woman free as Shannon fights for the rights of women and girls around the world. &nbsp
column11: Shannon writes regularly for Huffington Post and Matador Network, and is currently writing her first book. &nbsp
column12: She has been featured on<a style=""color: #c97320
column23: was in 2012 on the Power of Voice which best illustrates the thread that links all of her work together.<em>&nbsp
column25: She is the subject of the documentary film series,
column28: screening at film festivals throughout 2012 and 2013 and is working as the producer for the upcoming documentary,&nbsp
column30: based on the power of voice through the lens of Afghan photographers with Red Reel's, Alexandria Bombach to premier in 2013.

column20: >Heard the buzz about Lean Product Development? Got an idea that you want to bring to the market using Lean Product Development techniques? column2: >Scavenger Dash is a wildly fun urban adventure that is as much adventure race as it is scavenger hunt. Compare it to The Amazing Race, but on a local level, where anyone can participate!

>This incredible experience consists of teams of two that will solve clues, travel to local points of interest, and complete fun challenges while discovering the city in a whole new way. The race is around 5-8 miles long and will take 2-4 hours to complete. Teams may use public transportation, such as buses and trains but they may not use bicycles, cabs or private vehicles. All participants are encouraged to stick around for the fun party atmosphere and camaraderie after the event. So, if you like fun, adventure and making great memories, this is the event for you!

>Race check-in will open at 11:00am. There is a mandatory pre-event meeting at 11:45am that all participants must attend, so please plan on arriving for check-in by 11:30am. Event begins at noon and is officially over at 4pm. Please visit www.scavengerdash.com for more info, including FAQs and Rules
>No refunds given for any reason unless the race is cancelled by us.

column26: >Lead and inspire your team to standout performance!

column24: >gives you the process to work smarter not harder in developing high performance teams during this demanding business environment.

column23: >Teams and the people in them are responsible for the majority of highs and lows in the life of a leader and will often ultimately determine whether you peak or plummet as a leader.

>Teams are complex and require constant attention, however we all know that in an ever-evolving fast paced corporate environment there isn’t much time to ‘stop and smell the roses’. It is critical to form an air tight strategy to guarantee that your team operates at it’s peak in order to deliver exceptional results in a contracted business environment.

>This is something we know a lot about and have been helping many of Australia’s largest and most successful corporations with. We invite you to join us and tap into our breakthrough system for accelerating team performance.

>This 3-day intensive program has been honed to deliver the knowledge, tools and insights to boost team performance through refocusing and reinventing for success. By harnessing the intelligence of social, cognitive and behavioural neuroscience, the program delivers:

column4: >The capability to build an environment that leverages from the six drivers of high-performance teams
>The ability to identify and resolve the nine key conflict points that will destroy team cohesion
>The skills to recognise and cultivate the performance mindset that takes your people from battle mode to breakthrough problem-solving and strategic thinking.

column19: >Each module builds upon and expands your existing leadership skills and knowledge, providing practical insight and tools that can be rapidly deployed to fill your team’s self-identified blind spots and capability gaps.

column21: >If you would like to know more please click here to download a copy of the <a href=""https://dl.dropbox.com/u/30297529/NeuroPower%20Accelerated%20Teaming%20Program_Brisbane%20February%202013.pdf""><span style=""color: #0000ff
>Numbers are limited so be quick to reserve your spot and secure an early bird price!
>If you would like to speak to us to find out more information please call Zane on +61 400 719 422

column39: >NeuroPower is a behavioural strategy consultancy that specialises in applying the latest insights from neuroscience to drive individual, team and organisational performance.

column22: >The NeuroPower framework intertwines neuroscientific, behavioural and psychological perspectives into a model that addresses complex issues of the mind. It integrates historically siloed, and often contradictory, schools of thought in an insightful and practical way.
>Our consultancy uses the NeuroPower framework in a wide range of industries and organisations, in particular we apply the NeuroPower framework to:

column7: >Today, items from hand soap to tomatoes are labeled as “eco-friendly” or “sustainable,” but if everything is green, nothing really is. At a time when addressing global sustainability challenges is a priority for many brands, how do you engage and motivate consumers who have green fatigue? Join us for a conversation about communications clutter from experts in corporate sustainability and consumer marketing.

column5: >Tonight's host is

column8: >ANGIE HEAD
column10: >is a singer/songwriter/musician.
column12: >She is also a skillful teacher and practitioner of the martial arts.  A graduate of the University of Michigan with a degree in Ethnomusicology (the study of music on the context of cultures), Angie has played at Busboys and Poets and the Charm City Kitty Club.
